headline: Heard on the Street: Live Nation May Get Friendlier DOJ Crowd
summary: Lots of companies and industries are expecting a friendlier regulatory environment under the new Trump administration.  Live Nation Entertainment might have the most riding on it.  The parent company of Ticketmaster saw its shares rise nearly 5% on Tuesday after reporting better-than-expected revenue and operating earnings for the third quarter.

headline: Live Nation Stock Gains After Earnings Beat Forecasts
summary: Live Nation Entertainment, the world’s largest concert promoter, late Monday reported strong momentum after a massive summer concert season, and said it anticipates further growth in 2025.  Shares in Live Nation, which also owns Ticketmaster, gained nearly 5% in morning trading Tuesday.  Fans are paying more to attend shows and spending greater sums once they enter concert venues, the results showed.
